  ----------------------
  -knowledge statement
   --------------------------
  -Understanding risk assessment can be big help to the auditor.
  -Audits can be designed to take a risk-based approach.
  -Risk-based approach to auditing looks at more than just a risk , it also examine the company's practices
  -Its tolerance for the risk.
  -It can help in pinpointing area of  high risk.
  -It is based on determining which areas should be audited based on the perceived level of risk.
